01:16.573 --> 01:21.761
That is kind of talking about some of the next steps that we are going to be taking here as a church.

01:22.302 --> 01:24.686
We'll talk in more detail about that in a couple of weeks.

01:24.726 --> 01:30.957
But before we get into what we're going to do, we wanted to take a few weeks and be reminded of why we feel the need to do that.

01:30.997 --> 01:34.002
And thus, this message here for this week as well.

01:34.146 --> 02:01.330
In Ecclesiastes, Solomon says, there's nothing new under the sun, which is a fancy way of saying, if you hang around here long enough, you're gonna hear the same thing over and over and over again, because in some ways, if you've been around the well for any number of months, there are some passion areas that we are committed to here at the well, and we just feel the need, now and again, to bring them up just so we don't lose focus, just so we can be reminded, and in fact, in 2 Peter chapter 1,

02:01.666 --> 02:11.762
Peter says, therefore I will always be ready to remind you of these things as long as I'm in this earthly dwelling, I consider it right to stir you up, he said, by way of reminder.

02:12.243 --> 02:24.943
And so this week is gonna be one of those reminder messages as well, maybe for some, but for others, it might be new for you because there is a reality that we are experiencing together that is very, very unique.

02:25.003 --> 02:26.866
If you happen to be a guest here with us,

02:27.010 --> 02:31.356
We are experiencing a growth here at our church, like we've never seen before.

02:32.057 --> 02:36.764
And so in that, I think there's some uniquenesses to this season that we want to draw some attention to.

02:36.784 --> 02:41.991
And I'm going to just kind of play a little bit at all campuses and gathering, even those watching via video or out in the theater.

02:42.012 --> 02:44.074
I'm going to do a little raising of hands exercise.

02:44.135 --> 02:48.260
We don't do this very often, but it's going to require 100% participation.

02:48.301 --> 02:49.763
So if you'll do this with me, that would be great.

02:50.444 --> 02:54.930
If you have been here at the well for 23 years or less,

02:55.138 --> 02:57.522
I want you to raise your hand and keep it raised, okay?

02:57.962 --> 02:58.924
So we're gonna start there.

02:59.505 --> 03:00.867
Now, keep it raised.

03:01.007 --> 03:05.454
If you've been here 20 years or less, keep your hand raised.

03:05.474 --> 03:07.337
20 years or less, keep it raised.

03:07.357 --> 03:09.420
So all we lost there was the OGs, all right?

03:09.700 --> 03:10.602
People that were here from the beginning.

03:10.982 --> 03:13.746
If you've been here 15 years or less, keep it raised.

03:13.766 --> 03:17.072
10 years or less, keep your hand raised.

03:18.253 --> 03:20.136
Five years or less, keep your hand raised.

03:20.737 --> 03:23.922
If you've been here two years or less, keep your hand raised.

03:24.962 --> 03:31.210
So what I want you to see at all campuses and gatherings, at all venues, you can put your hands down now, thank you.

03:31.250 --> 03:37.317
There is a movement that has happened in the last couple of years that is pretty special.

03:37.918 --> 03:42.924
And through the last 10 years, we've been picking up more and more people, which is a wonderful problem to have.

03:42.964 --> 03:46.569
But in that, we have doubled in the last 18 months.

03:47.410 --> 03:51.415
Our kids ministry has grown by over 200%.

03:52.616 --> 03:53.938
Our student ministry

03:54.082 --> 03:54.903
by over 150%.

03:54.983 --> 03:57.586
Now bigger is not better.

03:58.006 --> 03:58.968
That's not what we're saying.

03:59.788 --> 04:05.815
But we're asking the question as we are growing as a movement, how do we steward what God is doing?

04:06.616 --> 04:12.863
How do we allow for growth to continue to come and yet maintain doctrinal faithfulness?

04:13.584 --> 04:15.526
How do we avoid mission drift?

04:16.167 --> 04:19.591
How do we stay focused on who we've been from the very beginning?

04:19.791 --> 04:22.354
And are there any examples in our Bible

04:22.594 --> 04:25.678
of what the early church did with that as well.

04:25.738 --> 04:30.664
And so thankfully, as you look at the book of Acts, there are some breadcrumbs left on the trail for us.

04:30.764 --> 04:34.429
And so that's why we want to kind of walk through a bit of an overview of the book.

04:34.449 --> 04:45.783
And we want to ask and answer the question, do we see any examples in our Bible of how a faith community that was growing rapidly handled growth and in that what they focused on?

04:46.424 --> 04:50.930
The movement of Christianity is a story of viral before viral was the thing.

04:51.522 --> 04:54.205
in that it started with one and that is Jesus Christ.

04:55.065 --> 04:58.749
Jesus is going to in the gospel accounts called 12 disciples.

04:59.590 --> 05:08.758
We're gonna see those 12 disciples and a gathering of others are gonna be sent out, the number that we're given is 70 that are sent out to proclaim the gospel.

05:09.399 --> 05:12.882
And so we've got now this movement that's beginning in the gospel accounts.

05:12.942 --> 05:18.728
Then in Matthew 16, Jesus speaks of a gathering of what he calls called out ones.

05:19.248 --> 05:20.850
The word is ecclesia.

05:20.994 --> 05:22.776
you know it in your Bible as church.

05:22.836 --> 05:35.251
He begins to talk about the ecclesia of God, the church of God that is being gathered together so that they can actually be trained, taught, trained, equipped, and discipled to go.

05:35.271 --> 05:38.876
The word ech means out from kaleto means to call.

05:38.916 --> 05:44.282
And so what we see is this movement of the church is actually the people, it's not a building.

05:45.243 --> 05:49.608
That we are the church, we don't necessarily go to church.

05:49.669 --> 05:50.930
Now it seems subtle,

05:51.490 --> 06:00.560
But the point is that these called out ones are to be taught, trained, equipped, and discipled so that they can influence the region.

06:00.580 --> 06:06.246
So it starts within a life, impacts a home, impacts a city, impacts a region.

06:06.266 --> 06:13.854
To the point where at the end of the Gospel of Matthew, Jesus gives what's called the Great Commission where he says, go therefore into all nations.

06:13.914 --> 06:18.699
Now the command in this passage is go therefore into all nations and make disciples.

06:19.260 --> 06:21.202
Make disciples is the command

06:21.314 --> 06:32.004
The assumption is you're going, as you're going, wherever you're going, of course, assuming you're going, make disciples and baptizing them in the name of the Father, the Son, and the Holy Spirit.

06:32.024 --> 06:35.487
He says, and then teaching them to obey all I've commanded you.

06:35.507 --> 06:36.849
And so a disciple is interesting.

06:36.869 --> 06:41.653
The word disciple comes to the word mathetes and it means a student or a pupil.

06:41.773 --> 06:51.122
Now in our context, a student or a pupil is one who sits in class, hears from a teacher or a professor, a set of data,

06:51.458 --> 07:03.393
processes that data and is able, at some point, to regurgitate that data, whether it's a test or a paper or whatever, meaning it shows their ability to absorb data and repeat that data.

07:03.533 --> 07:05.015
That's not what a disciple is.

07:05.776 --> 07:17.490
Though a disciple is a pupil or a student, there's an assumption, not simply of the regurgitation of data, but not just that you would know what your rabbi knew, but that you would live as your rabbi lived.

07:18.531 --> 07:20.594
It's both orthodoxy

07:20.706 --> 07:21.888
and orthopraxie.

07:22.629 --> 07:24.833
It's both belief and behavior.

07:25.574 --> 07:27.177
It's both knowing and doing.

07:27.678 --> 07:34.089
There's an assumption that it's not just about the data set, it's about how that data set informs how you actually live.

07:34.830 --> 07:36.533
And so that's what Jesus invites us into.

07:36.553 --> 07:38.456
And so now we come to the book of Acts chapter one.

07:39.137 --> 07:46.770
And in verses six and following, the disciples, having now seen the risen Christ, ask a very, very logical question.

07:47.170 --> 07:51.678
Having just conquered death, which is rad, is this the time you're gonna restore your kingdom?

07:52.399 --> 07:54.022
And the answer is interesting in verse seven.

07:54.042 --> 08:04.459
He says, it's not for you to know the times of the seasons that are fixed by the Father's authority, but you will receive power when the Spirit comes upon you, which means you don't have it yet.

08:05.361 --> 08:10.770
And you will be when that Spirit comes upon you and you do receive power, you will be my witnesses.

08:11.042 --> 08:12.885
The word witness is the word Martus.

08:12.965 --> 08:14.227
It's where we get the word martyr.

08:14.707 --> 08:17.171
But it doesn't simply mean one who lays down their life.

08:17.491 --> 08:20.596
It means one who testifies, one who proclaims.

08:21.057 --> 08:29.429
You will be my Martus in Jerusalem, Judea, Samaria, and the remotest parts of the earth.

08:29.569 --> 08:30.330
It's an indicative.

08:30.350 --> 08:31.692
It's not an imperative command.

08:31.712 --> 08:34.556
So he's not saying, make sure you go in this order.

08:34.977 --> 08:36.379
Make sure you end up in these places.

08:36.619 --> 08:38.642
It's just saying, this is what's going to happen.

08:39.010 --> 08:46.581
And sure enough, the rest of the book of Acts is showing you how that exact thing took place, that the gospel did begin to move.

08:46.701 --> 08:52.349
And as it moved, what you're gonna find is the numbers begin to grow very, very quickly.

08:52.690 --> 09:03.565
In fact, if you look at chapter one, verse 15, we went from one to 12 to 70 to now in Acts chapter one, verse 15, there's 120 that assemble in the upper room.

09:03.585 --> 09:07.090
In chapter two, the spirit of God has poured out upon the early church,

09:07.458 --> 09:12.905
Peter preaches a bang-up message, invites people to repent for the kingdom of heaven is at hand.

09:13.325 --> 09:18.752
And if you look at chapter two of the book of Acts, verse 41, it's beginning to now get out of hand.

09:19.813 --> 09:26.541
It says those who had received the word were baptized, and that day there was added about how many does your Bible say?

09:26.561 --> 09:27.963
About 3,000 souls.

09:28.003 --> 09:33.790
Now I'm so thankful this passage is in here because I talk to people now and again who, ah, you know, I tried coming to the web, but I don't like it.

09:33.810 --> 09:34.411
It's too big.

09:35.492 --> 09:37.234
They say, well, I'm not into a mega church.

09:37.762 --> 09:41.927
I'm like, well, I appreciate that, but you wouldn't have liked the original church there.

09:41.947 --> 09:47.634
Because by even modern day standards, this was a mega church several times over.

09:48.075 --> 09:49.677
The issue's really not size, is it?

09:49.697 --> 09:50.718
The issue's intimacy.

09:51.439 --> 09:52.661
The issue is, can I feel connected?

09:53.582 --> 09:54.303
Can I feel known?

09:54.823 --> 09:56.385
Can I feel like I'm a part of something?

09:57.266 --> 10:00.250
And in that regard, I don't like a large church either.

10:00.851 --> 10:03.815
If by large you mean easy to hide, I feel alone.

10:03.935 --> 10:04.856
Nobody knows my name.

10:04.916 --> 10:06.578
If something happens to me, nobody cares.

10:06.882 --> 10:12.107
If that's the case, I don't like large either, but that's not what the church is, and hopefully it's not who we are.

10:12.507 --> 10:22.797
If you look at verse 42, notice what they were daily committing themselves to for very strategic things, the apostles teaching, the fellowship, the breaking of bread, and the prayer.

10:23.358 --> 10:29.243
Now what I want you to notice in verse 42 is how simple the church was in the book of Acts.

10:30.665 --> 10:36.370
Nobody's lighting themselves on fire to draw a crowd, okay, they're not super impressive,

10:36.706 --> 10:41.831
They're not launching strategic ministry growth engines so that we can reach this demographic.

10:41.851 --> 10:44.334
They're not driven by market share.

10:44.975 --> 10:49.179
They're not saying, hey, what marketing campaign could we do that we might reach these people?

10:49.820 --> 10:53.183
They're not really driven by business principles at all.

10:53.243 --> 10:54.825
In fact, they're just teaching their Bible.

10:55.566 --> 10:58.008
They're spending time in a reciprocal relationship.

10:58.028 --> 10:59.730
That's what fellowship or cornea means.

11:00.391 --> 11:03.474
They're spending time in prayer.

11:03.842 --> 11:07.445
and they're spending time enjoying meals and enjoying the Lord's Supper together.

11:07.465 --> 11:11.890
It's very, very simple, but in verse 43, everyone kept feeling a sense of what?

11:13.191 --> 11:17.815
Oh, which just means I can't explain what's happening here.

11:18.516 --> 11:21.499
I can't tell you why the early church is growing.

11:21.579 --> 11:23.481
I can't explain to you exactly what's happening.

11:23.801 --> 11:25.362
All I know is it's not about us.

11:26.003 --> 11:30.267
I cannot tell you how many times I've reminded our staff it is not about us.

11:30.848 --> 11:31.929
I don't know what God's doing.

11:32.089 --> 11:33.490
I don't know why he's doing it.

11:33.570 --> 11:34.551
It is awe.

11:35.392 --> 11:41.440
And if you look at verse 46, day by day, they're continuing with one mind in the temple and are together in houses.

11:41.961 --> 11:54.397
Like we'd love to think that we created, hey, let's do life in a gathering, let's do life in groups and teams, but we're literally ripping it off from the early church who assembled corporately together and then they did life in smaller groups.

11:54.477 --> 11:56.299
Why do you do life in a group or a team?

11:56.319 --> 11:58.622
Why do you do life meeting in house to house?

11:58.642 --> 11:59.784
Because that's where you could be known.

12:00.625 --> 12:01.586
That's where you can be.

12:01.666 --> 12:02.187
connected.

12:02.227 --> 12:08.537
And in verse 47, they're praising God and they're experiencing favor with all, which means believers and unbelievers.

12:08.617 --> 12:13.686
And notice the Lord was adding to their number day by day those who are being saved.

12:13.806 --> 12:18.113
There is something ridiculously magnetic about an authentic Christian.

12:19.315 --> 12:24.744
When you not only know what Jesus taught, but you live like Jesus lived, that changes everything.

12:25.626 --> 12:28.370
Because you now are putting on display the gospel.

12:28.834 --> 12:31.717
And so fast forward to chapter four, look at verse four.

12:32.417 --> 12:40.745
It went from one to 12 to 70 to 120 to 3,000 to an ax four, verse four, how many do you see there?

12:40.765 --> 12:41.986
5,000.

12:42.006 --> 12:44.068
So now it's really growing.

12:44.669 --> 12:54.478
And in verse 14, it says, and all the more believers, or all the more believers in the Lord, multitudes of men and women were constantly added to their number.

12:55.179 --> 12:58.802
So it's 5,000 and climbing.

12:59.074 --> 13:07.605
Chapter five, there's an opposition that arises, and they're trying to, they, the religious leader, Jewish religious leaders at least, are trying to squash the movement of the gospel.

13:07.625 --> 13:08.967
They're like, this thing's getting out of hand.

13:09.547 --> 13:13.452
And so they go to get some advice from one of the sages of their days, named was Gamaliel.

13:13.913 --> 13:17.618
Now Gamaliel had a student whose name was Saul of Tarsus.

13:17.698 --> 13:19.921
We're gonna learn about him in chapter nine.

13:19.961 --> 13:26.609
He becomes the apostle Paul who writes in our Bible about two thirds of your New Testament and plants churches all over the ancient world.

13:26.629 --> 13:27.410
But before that,

13:28.002 --> 13:35.654
He's mentored by Gamalia, and they say, hey, what do you say we do with this movement of followers of Jesus?

13:35.674 --> 13:39.320
And he goes, well, you've got two choices, and neither one of them's good.

13:39.520 --> 13:45.470
You can let it go and see what happens, because if it's not of God, it's gonna go away.

13:46.812 --> 13:54.524
But if it is of God, it's gonna continue to grow, and if you oppose it, you're gonna find yourself fighting against God.

13:54.564 --> 13:55.826
And so he says, either way,

13:55.906 --> 13:58.169
You just need to let this thing play out.

13:58.970 --> 14:07.162
And so what happens is the church continues to grow, but it brings in chapter six, very interesting complexity.

14:07.723 --> 14:15.234
You've got two groups of widows that as the church is growing are fighting together over the distribution of food.

14:15.935 --> 14:17.558
And it's an ethnic thing.

14:17.578 --> 14:20.562
They're concerned that the Grecian widows are being overlooked,

14:20.866 --> 14:23.008
and the Hebraic widows are being shown preference.

14:23.328 --> 14:27.833
And what you find in this chapter is in an interesting shift the disciples make.

14:27.853 --> 14:31.936
And it begins to show you what they're thinking about as the church grows.

14:32.377 --> 14:38.182
And they say, look, the serving of these ladies is very important, but time is a zero sum game.

14:38.783 --> 14:47.511
So if we choose to serve these ladies, we're gonna neglect the word of God in prayer, which is a priority for us as we assemble.

14:47.852 --> 14:48.832
And so here's what we're gonna do.

14:48.872 --> 14:50.514
We're gonna raise up servants

14:50.722 --> 14:52.324
comes from the Greek word diakonai.

14:52.344 --> 14:55.269
You may have heard of churches that have deacons.

14:55.890 --> 15:08.569
Those are just people that serve the practical needs of the people that are there, so that church leadership, whether it's pastors or whatever, can study and teach, pray and teach, handle the word of God.

15:08.730 --> 15:17.063
And the theme throughout is teaching, training, equipping and discipling is a priority as the church continues to grow.

15:17.443 --> 15:19.346
And so in verse seven of chapter six,

15:20.002 --> 15:22.326
Because of this, the Word of God kept on spreading.

15:22.366 --> 15:28.296
The numbers of disciples continue to increase greatly in Jerusalem, even to the point where priests now were coming to faith.

15:28.396 --> 15:32.162
Well, in chapter seven, the first Christian martyr, Stephen, is killed.

15:33.003 --> 15:36.729
And his execution is orchestrated by that student of Gamaliel.

15:37.150 --> 15:39.033
His name is Saul from the city of Tarsus.

15:39.714 --> 15:47.026
Now, thankfully for us, in chapter nine, this Saul of Tarsus has a faith encounter with Jesus Christ.

15:47.394 --> 15:54.885
And in verses 19 and 20 of Acts chapter nine, he begins to proclaim Jesus as the Son of God.

15:55.505 --> 16:01.854
Now, his ministry, interestingly enough, does not go well initially, neither in Damascus nor in Jerusalem.

16:01.875 --> 16:11.068
And we get a little bit of a glimpse, according to Galatians chapter one, verse 17, it tells us that this guy, after he places his faith in Christ, his world is upside down.

16:11.688 --> 16:15.634
He's passionately taught the Hebrew scriptures, your Old Testament forever.

16:15.746 --> 16:20.593
And now he's like, how did I not see Jesus who every story whispers his name?

16:20.893 --> 16:33.170
So he spends three years in the desert of Arabia with his Bible, filling in the blanks as to what he missed, and then goes back to his hometown of Tarsus, which will be significant here in just a moment.

16:33.190 --> 16:35.714
Well, in verse 31, meanwhile, the church continues to grow.

16:36.375 --> 16:42.644
It says, the church throughout all Judea and Galilee and Samaria and enjoyed peace, because he's now trusted Christ and is gone.

16:43.204 --> 16:44.306
It's being built up

16:44.610 --> 16:50.037
and it's going on in the fear of the Lord and in the comfort of the Holy Spirit and it continued to increase.

16:50.859 --> 16:52.901
And then begin to move even more geographically.

16:52.921 --> 17:00.311
In chapter 11, verse 21, the church is going to begin to now go north and it's in a city called Antioch.

17:00.351 --> 17:01.593
It's in modern day Syria.

17:02.314 --> 17:08.803
And as it goes north in verse 21, it says a large number who believed turned to the Lord.

17:08.823 --> 17:11.346
So the gospel now has jumped ethnic fences.

17:12.067 --> 17:13.970
It's now in Syrian Antioch.

17:14.146 --> 17:19.133
You've got Gentiles coming to faith in mass and the church in Jerusalem hears about it.

17:19.533 --> 17:23.899
Now they didn't plan this, they didn't ask for this, but this is happening.

17:24.460 --> 17:30.188
And so in verses 22 and following, the news reaches the church in Jerusalem, they go, hey, we gotta do a little quality control.

17:30.468 --> 17:33.633
Are these people following the same Jesus we're talking about?

17:33.653 --> 17:34.754
Barnabas, go check it out.

17:35.295 --> 17:40.402
So Barnabas gets in the freeway, heads north, goes up to Antioch and sees what's happening there.

17:40.738 --> 17:43.822
And when he arrives in verse 23, he witnesses the grace of God.

17:43.862 --> 17:48.509
He rejoices and encourages them with resolute heart to remain true to the Lord.

17:48.529 --> 17:49.510
He goes, this is legit.

17:49.830 --> 17:51.052
You guys are following Jesus.

17:51.412 --> 17:52.394
This is amazing.

17:52.894 --> 17:58.662
In verse 24, it finishes there within considerable numbers now were brought to the Lord.

17:58.742 --> 18:01.126
Barnabas though realizes he's got a problem.

18:01.626 --> 18:08.676
Because you've got a church now in the city of Antioch who doesn't have anybody to teach, train, equip or disciple.

18:08.916 --> 18:10.258
And that's not who he is.

18:10.754 --> 18:11.635
He's an encourager.

18:12.135 --> 18:12.956
He's not a teacher.

18:13.276 --> 18:15.719
So he's looking around going, man, we got a thriving church up here.

18:16.239 --> 18:19.582
Is there anybody in the area that we could find who could teach these people?

18:19.602 --> 18:26.349
Is there any gifted communicator who knows his Bible that we could find and just up the freeway as Tarsus?

18:26.990 --> 18:40.082
And so if you look, in fact, at verses 25 and following, he goes now to Tarsus, he looks for Saul and when he found him, he brought him to Antioch and for an entire year,

18:40.450 --> 18:49.023
Saul of Tarsus, we know him as the Apostle Paul, spends time teaching, training, equipping, and discipling in the city of Antioch.

18:49.043 --> 18:59.819
And it is so effective that that passage finishes in verse 25 with the disciples were first called Christians in Antioch, which begs the question, what is a Christian?

19:00.780 --> 19:06.368
A Christian is someone who not only knew what Jesus knew, but lived the way Jesus lived.

19:06.849 --> 19:10.194
And to the people living in Antioch, they didn't have a category

19:10.338 --> 19:14.302
or a name in which to call the people that looked like Jesus the Christ.

19:15.043 --> 19:16.285
And so they go, well, who are these people?

19:16.305 --> 19:17.025
They go, look, I don't know.

19:17.326 --> 19:20.329
But I know that they used to live one way and now they live different.

19:20.609 --> 19:22.932
And they say they have a new life because of the Christ.

19:23.713 --> 19:25.595
And they've been transformed because of the Christ.

19:26.096 --> 19:28.198
And they live differently because of the Christ.

19:28.458 --> 19:31.662
They are Christ-like ones, which is what a Christian is.

19:32.242 --> 19:37.008
And so they're called Christians because of teaching, training, equipping, and discipling.

19:37.849 --> 19:39.090
And in chapter 13,

19:39.170 --> 19:40.391
Something beautiful happens.

19:41.032 --> 19:44.475
The apostles are like, hey, this gospel is reaching Gentiles.

19:44.515 --> 19:46.758
We need to officially send some people out.

19:46.798 --> 19:53.445
So they send out Paul, and they send out Barnabas, and they go on their first missionary journey into modern day Turkey.

19:53.885 --> 19:54.606
And what do they do?

19:55.066 --> 20:02.474
Teach, train, equip, and disciple, and in that plant churches, like the Church of Galatia, which has a book in your Bible written to them.

20:02.914 --> 20:04.416
The Church of Colossae, same.

20:04.796 --> 20:06.418
The Church of Ephesus, same.

20:06.754 --> 20:09.477
Other churches mentioned Laodicea and Hierapolis.

20:09.557 --> 20:12.460
That entire region now, churches are being started.

20:12.840 --> 20:16.064
And if you look at chapter 13 verse 44, how effective was it?

20:17.125 --> 20:24.392
What says, well, on the next Sabbath day, chapter 13 verse 44, nearly the entire city gathered to hear the word of the Lord.

20:25.694 --> 20:27.335
The whole city shows up.

20:27.375 --> 20:29.718
Who are these guys and what are they talking about?

20:29.738 --> 20:30.579
And what did they do?

20:30.839 --> 20:33.682
They taught, they trained, they quipped, and they discipled.

20:34.434 --> 20:40.541
Look at verses 48 and 49, it not only impacts that city, it impacts the entire region.

20:40.581 --> 20:44.225
The word of the Lord was being spread throughout the whole region.

20:44.685 --> 20:54.556
You're talking about a geographic region called Asia Minor, the entire nation of modern day Turkey plus some Armenia and heading now into Syria.

20:54.776 --> 20:58.400
You've got a whole region being influenced now by the gospel.

20:58.520 --> 21:00.242
And in chapter 14, verse one,

21:00.834 --> 21:04.139
It says in Iconium, they entered the synagogue where the Jews were together.

21:04.179 --> 21:10.189
They spoke in such a manner that a large number of people believed both Jews and Greeks.

21:10.269 --> 21:16.259
And so now, chapter 15, the disciples call them back home and say, okay, we need to talk about this.

21:16.419 --> 21:21.648
It's the first church council before the council of Ephesus or Calcedon or Nicaea.

21:22.369 --> 21:26.175
They do a first church council and they say, okay, what are we gonna do here, guys?

21:26.215 --> 21:28.018
The gospel's going to Gentiles.

21:28.162 --> 21:29.444
They go, yeah, this is great.

21:29.624 --> 21:36.011
Meanwhile, Paul and Barnabas in verse 35, while this is all being decided, stayed in Antioch doing what?

21:36.953 --> 21:38.474
Teaching and preaching.

21:39.576 --> 21:43.521
And so the second missionary journey is launched out from Antioch.

21:43.561 --> 21:56.156
Now, logically, if you're the Apostle Paul and you just went into modern day Turkey and planted Galatia, Colossi and Ephesus and people were coming to faith so that the entire region was impacted, where would you go?

21:56.496 --> 21:57.938
Well, you would probably go there.

21:58.466 --> 22:07.317
And so if you look now in chapter 16, verse five, the churches are being strengthened in faith and increasing in number daily.

22:07.357 --> 22:10.721
They go back and encourage the churches that were there.

22:10.822 --> 22:14.666
And then in verse 10, something very strange happens.

22:14.686 --> 22:27.122
We don't know exactly what mechanically this looked like, but if you look at the context of chapter 16 following verse five, the spirit forbid him from going back to the places he already went to.

22:27.682 --> 22:30.405
and then the spirit of Jesus forbid him to do it.

22:30.425 --> 22:39.173
Now, we don't know what that looked like, but for some reason, it's as if God's saying, I've got something else for you, don't just rinse and repeat what you've already done.

22:39.653 --> 22:41.295
And I think the key is in verse 10.

22:41.875 --> 22:48.221
He sees a vision of a man from Macedonia, which is Greek controlled land, Macedonia and the K.I.

22:48.542 --> 22:50.183
all controlled by the Greeks.

22:50.203 --> 22:54.227
And so he sees a vision of a Macedonian man who says, come over here and help us.

22:54.407 --> 22:55.348
And so he goes.

22:56.009 --> 22:57.330
And in chapter 16,

22:58.114 --> 23:01.458
Now we see people in a city called Philippi embrace the gospel.

23:02.099 --> 23:05.443
In chapter 17, people in Thessalonica embrace the gospel.

23:06.164 --> 23:08.727
Again, people of Berea embrace the gospel.

23:08.807 --> 23:11.050
People in Athens embrace the gospel.

23:11.230 --> 23:14.734
And then in chapter 18, people in Corinth embrace the gospel.

23:15.275 --> 23:22.964
And in fact, Acts 18, 8 says many of the Corinthians when they heard were believed and baptized.

23:22.984 --> 23:24.466
Now you've got the entire

23:24.802 --> 23:41.167
region now over the sea there in Macedonia and decay all of them now being influenced by the gospel and in verse 18 or verse 11 rather of chapter 18 notice the Apostle Paul stays in the city of Corinth for 18 months.

23:41.748 --> 23:45.574
Now that'll be significant here in just a moment but remember that as we continue on.

23:46.054 --> 23:49.139
Why would you spend 18 months in a city?

23:49.940 --> 23:53.746
You're teaching, you're training, you're equipping, you're discipling.

23:54.306 --> 23:56.769
Now the third missionary journey is Acts 19.

23:58.412 --> 24:01.456
And the focus really of the third journey is the city of Ephesus.

24:02.036 --> 24:08.105
And if you look at verses nine and 10, some were becoming hardened and disobedient.

24:08.145 --> 24:10.307
Keep in mind, it was not all awesome.

24:11.289 --> 24:16.556
The journey of proclaiming the gospel in these various regions was not always well received.

24:16.656 --> 24:24.146
Paul was gonna speak of his imprisonments and his beatings and his difficulties and his shipwreck journeys and his hardships.

24:24.354 --> 24:43.233
But if you look at verse 10, he's there for two years, it says, and all who lived in Asia now heard the word of the Lord, both Jews and Greek, and if you drop down to chapter 20 verse 31, he's not simply an Ephesus for two years, it says he spends a full three years in Ephesus.

24:43.614 --> 24:48.198
He starts a seminary at the school of Tyrannus, and what is he doing for three years in Ephesus?

24:48.639 --> 24:51.922
Teaching, training, equipping, and discipling.

24:52.130 --> 24:55.473
And then one final passage, look at chapter 21, verse 10.

24:56.014 --> 24:56.835
I'm sorry, verse 20.

24:57.355 --> 24:59.137
Chapter 21, verse 20.

25:01.900 --> 25:10.889
He says, when they heard, they began glorifying God, and they said to him, you see, brother, how many thousands there are among the Jews and those who have believed.

25:11.550 --> 25:14.913
Now, some of your Bibles may have a note on how many thousands.

25:15.614 --> 25:17.876
And if so, it may say 10 thousands.

25:18.597 --> 25:19.378
Point is,

25:19.586 --> 25:36.413
We don't know exactly how many thousands are represented here, but texturally, it could be as many as 10,000, which means the church had grown exponentially from one to 12 to 70 to 120 to 3,000 to 5,000 to another number here of maybe as many as 10,000.

25:36.433 --> 25:37.655
Now, what's the point?

25:38.496 --> 25:44.045
Why walk through the book of Acts and why show the numeric growth of the early church?

25:44.065 --> 25:47.090
Well, I think the principle is undeniably evident

25:47.554 --> 25:56.932
that the larger the church became, the more intentional their focus seemed to be on teaching, training, equipping, and discipling.

25:57.092 --> 25:57.393
Why?

25:58.194 --> 26:08.434
Because as you taught, trained, equipped, and discipled, a life was changed and a family was influenced and a neighborhood was influenced.

26:08.674 --> 26:18.507
and a city was influenced, and a region was influenced, and a world was influenced, influenced by teaching, training, equipping, and discipling.

26:19.328 --> 26:28.180
And so we see the early church as it grew, as it said it would in Acts 1, 8, from Jerusalem to Judea to Samaria to the remotest parts of the earth.

26:28.581 --> 26:38.194
As the church grew geographically and grew numerically, churches in cities became hubs, equipping hubs, gospel transformation,

26:38.370 --> 26:39.672
hubs and we see them.

26:40.013 --> 26:41.295
Jerusalem is the first.

26:42.197 --> 26:49.270
And then it went north to Antioch where Paul hung out for a full year with Barnabas teaching those people where they were first called Christians.

26:49.470 --> 26:53.998
Then it goes to Ephesus where for three years Paul teaches, trains, equips, and disciples.

26:54.279 --> 26:59.268
Then it goes to Corinth where he spends 18 months teaching, training, equipping, and discipling.

26:59.548 --> 27:02.674
We know as we finish the book of Acts it ends up being Rome.

27:02.786 --> 27:08.272
Rome became an equipping hub for teaching, training, equipping, and discipling.

27:08.292 --> 27:10.815
Do we see that pattern as church history continues?

27:11.896 --> 27:21.668
Yes, the gospel is going to go into Africa, and you're going to see the rise of Alexandria, Carthage, and Ethiopia teaching, training, equipping, and discipling.

27:22.188 --> 27:28.075
The continent of Europe is influenced as the continent of Asia was by the only city on the planet on two continents.

27:28.896 --> 27:30.578
It's known as Constantinople.

27:31.170 --> 27:33.973
or Byzantium, or you might know it today, is Istanbul.

27:33.993 --> 27:36.116
It's the only city on two continents.

27:36.136 --> 27:38.279
Both regions influenced by this city.

27:38.319 --> 27:38.859
What's the point?

27:39.120 --> 27:50.874
The point is these teaching centers, these equipping hubs, these churches became influential for the region in teaching, training, equipping, and discipling.

27:51.295 --> 27:56.041
And so the larger the church got, the more focused they became on those things.

27:56.181 --> 27:57.202
Why is that important?

27:57.698 --> 28:00.261
Well, I want to look at two additional passages if we can.

28:00.461 --> 28:01.863
One is in Romans chapter 12.

28:02.723 --> 28:03.604
Romans chapter 12.

28:04.145 --> 28:07.068
Why is it important to teach, train, equip, and disciple?

28:07.168 --> 28:12.894
Well, we are inviting people into the messy process of life with God together.

28:13.355 --> 28:17.099
And it is by its very nature unnatural.

28:18.400 --> 28:22.505
We are habituated apart from the work of the gospel to live in flesh.

28:23.766 --> 28:25.308
We are driven by indulgence.

28:25.628 --> 28:27.250
We are driven by desire.

28:27.522 --> 28:33.770
We are driven by preference, by the base drives of who we are on the inside.

28:34.711 --> 28:36.293
And they come natural to us.

28:37.254 --> 28:39.257
We are given to those things.

28:39.517 --> 28:43.021
But if we have embraced the gospel, we are no longer in flesh.

28:43.422 --> 28:50.570
We are now in spirit, which means we're having to retrain that my normal instinct when cut off in traffic might be that.

28:52.313 --> 28:53.374
But now I'm in Christ.

28:53.815 --> 28:56.658
And even though I feel that inclination, I go, no, no, no.

28:57.058 --> 28:57.879
I'm in Christ.

28:58.460 --> 29:06.969
And so Romans chapter 12, Paul is writing about how we respond to this unnatural invitation to life in the spirit.

29:07.430 --> 29:14.918
After 11 chapters of really good theology, by the way, the first 11 chapters of Romans are all of what God did for us.

29:15.619 --> 29:21.746
He says now in chapter 12 verse 1, therefore, I urge you brethren by the mercies of God to present yourself

29:21.858 --> 29:25.523
to God as a living sacrifice, holy and acceptable to Him.

29:25.563 --> 29:27.505
This is your spiritual service of worship.

29:27.525 --> 29:32.191
Paul saying, based on 11 chapters of what God did for you, what's the least you could do in return?

29:33.452 --> 29:34.894
Well, just offer yourself to Him.

29:35.675 --> 29:38.459
And say, based on what God has done for me, I live for Him now.

29:38.479 --> 29:39.440
I don't live for myself.

29:39.820 --> 29:42.103
I live for Him who died and rose again on my behalf.

29:42.163 --> 29:44.186
I offer myself to Him.

29:45.067 --> 29:50.994
And he says then in verse two, and do not be conformed any longer to the patterns of this world.

29:51.138 --> 29:52.159
What does that assume?

29:52.440 --> 29:56.686
It assumes, apart from the work of the gospel, I am conformed to the patterns of this world.

29:57.507 --> 30:09.183
I'm shoved into the world's mold, which is exactly what that word means, to be shoved into a way of living that the world says is right, but it's not right, because I'm in Christ now.

30:09.744 --> 30:15.211
So he says, don't be conformed any longer to the patterns of this world, but be transformed.

30:15.291 --> 30:17.394
Notice it doesn't say transform yourself.

30:18.562 --> 30:19.664
Be transformed.

30:20.164 --> 30:27.676
Something is going to be changing you, transforming you, informing you to live differently.

30:27.816 --> 30:28.236
What is it?

30:28.277 --> 30:28.937
Look at the text.

30:29.378 --> 30:30.760
Be transformed by what?

30:31.622 --> 30:32.623
The renewing of your mind.

30:33.665 --> 30:37.691
Teaching, training, equipping, and making disciples.

30:37.711 --> 30:42.598
As we are taught, trained, equipped, and discipled, we begin to understand what the Word of God says.

30:42.638 --> 30:45.362
Now, the Word of God informs the way I live.

30:46.402 --> 30:52.090
energized by the Spirit of God, in line with the Word of God, together with the people of God, we live distinctly.

30:52.310 --> 30:54.433
We're not shoved into the world's mold anymore.

30:55.535 --> 30:56.756
We don't live like that anymore.

30:56.796 --> 31:09.133
It's different because we've been taught and trained, but it is unnatural, which is why we have to be so focused on it because mission drift from the Word of God is so easy to do.

31:10.014 --> 31:15.602
We hold to the Scriptures and they're like, ah, I mean, there's a long time ago

31:15.874 --> 31:17.156
It's a progressive day today.

31:17.176 --> 31:18.938
I mean, come on, surely that doesn't apply today.

31:19.278 --> 31:21.461
And we begin to drift from what the word of God says.

31:22.082 --> 31:30.052
And so we as a hub of gospel transformation need to continually teach, train, equip and disciple.

31:30.072 --> 31:32.476
Turn to one more passage, Ephesians chapter four.

31:34.238 --> 31:35.199
Ephesians chapter four.

31:37.322 --> 31:42.549
One of the reasons we assemble as a church body is to live out what Ephesians four says.

31:42.609 --> 31:43.570
Remember, Ephesus,

31:43.970 --> 31:46.052
was one of those hubs for three years.

31:46.132 --> 31:50.897
Paul started a seminary there, trained people there on how to follow Jesus.

31:50.957 --> 31:58.425
And he says in verse 11 of Ephesians 4, there are roles that are given to the established, or to establish the church.

31:58.465 --> 32:04.572
He gave some as apostles, some as prophets, some as evangelists, and some as pastors and teachers.

32:04.632 --> 32:07.695
So these roles were given to the early church.

32:07.995 --> 32:10.418
What were they primarily called to do?

32:11.234 --> 32:13.556
to equip the saints for the work of service.

32:13.756 --> 32:15.298
Now why is that significant?

32:15.318 --> 32:27.550
The word equip comes from the word that means in some ways to mend a net, to make something that was useful, that wasn't useful because it was broken, mended so it can be useful again.

32:27.590 --> 32:37.079
The purpose of a church, of leadership at least at a church, is not to do the work of the ministry, it's to train and equip the body to do the work of the ministry.

32:37.319 --> 32:37.559
Why?

32:37.880 --> 32:40.242
Because you can't staff a church

32:40.514 --> 32:45.319
sufficient enough to handle the growth with a team of staff.

32:45.720 --> 32:47.401
You've got to have the body that responds.

32:48.603 --> 32:50.525
Remember, we are the church.

32:50.545 --> 32:54.949
So if we have a problem with volunteers in youth ministry, we have a problem.

32:55.850 --> 32:59.695
If we have a problem with volunteers in kids ministry, we have a problem.

32:59.855 --> 33:00.936
We are the church.

33:01.657 --> 33:08.985
And the role of the church by way of leadership is to train, teach, train, equip, and disciple so that we could do the work of ministry.

33:09.645 --> 33:10.386
And he says,

33:10.594 --> 33:17.341
to equip the saints for the work of ministry, for the building up of the body of Christ, that the church would be strengthened together until.

33:17.762 --> 33:30.476
So we continue to do this, until we all attain to the unity of the faith, which means there's a sense of oneness together, of solidarity together as to who God is and what the gospel is and the implications it has on our life.

33:30.896 --> 33:39.986
And until we all attain to the knowledge of the Son of God that we might be more like Jesus, to a mature man or woman so that we're growing together,

33:40.674 --> 33:50.064
individually to the measure in the statue which belongs to the fullness of Christ that we're putting on full display the glory of the gospel in a transformed life.

33:50.765 --> 33:57.833
As a result, verse 14, we will no longer be like children tossed here and there by waves.

33:58.954 --> 34:04.700
So the ultimate goal is that we wouldn't any longer be tossed like children here and there by wife.

34:04.740 --> 34:06.282
Have you ever seen a toddler in the ocean?

34:07.283 --> 34:10.226
I mean, fund a video unless it's your kid, then it's terrifying.

34:10.914 --> 34:14.399
because they're one distracted moment away from getting completely clobbered.

34:15.100 --> 34:32.786
And he's saying, the reason we teach, train, equip, and disciple is so that we won't be theological infants tossed here and there by every wave of TikTok, by every wave of some online person who has a podcast, we won't be

34:32.898 --> 34:45.831
tossed here and there by every theological wave of some person who wrote a book that sounded interesting and it had good marketing and so people are buying it as if it's awesome and it's awful and it's shoving you into the mold of the world.

34:45.892 --> 34:59.826
No, no, we teach, train, equip and disciple so that we're no longer children, which means we were, but that we would no longer be children tossed here and there by waves carried around by every wind of doctrine by the trickery of mid-craftiness

35:00.130 --> 35:03.095
of deceitful scheming, but instead, verse 15.

35:04.097 --> 35:10.547
Speaking the truth in love, we are to grow up into all aspects into Him who is the head, even Christ.

35:11.308 --> 35:20.524
That we, because we have been taught and trained and equipped and discipled, could actually speak truth in love to one another and say, no, no, no, the word of God says this.

35:21.265 --> 35:21.986
Let's do this.

35:22.126 --> 35:26.834
Now, why do we share this message in this season of this church?

35:27.522 --> 35:31.267
Well, there's no question we are experiencing some capacity issues.

35:31.287 --> 35:35.131
Some of you felt that at whatever campus or gathering you're at, just trying to park.

35:36.413 --> 35:42.080
And so there's a temptation to just continue to make room, make room, make room, make room, make room.

35:42.200 --> 35:45.684
And at some point, we will eventually need to do that.

35:46.565 --> 35:48.467
But we don't think we need to do that yet.

35:49.348 --> 35:57.298
And the reason would be, I think the only thing that would be worse than doubling in the last 18 months would be doubling again.

35:58.562 --> 36:12.284
and running the risk of mission drift or running the risk of not having people who are taught, trained, equipped, and discipled, pouring into our kids and pouring into our students or pouring into us.

36:13.325 --> 36:18.093
That we would have people that might queue up to be in a life group and we'd say, I'm so sorry, we don't have enough leaders.

36:19.035 --> 36:26.226
And so what we decided to do eventual as that move might be to build a sanctuary here at Clovis or make more room at our other campuses.

36:26.402 --> 36:41.977
We think that the right move for us to do next is to say, well, let's take the next season and let's teach and train and equip and disciple so that if God continues to grow our church, we grow not only numerically but in depth.

36:42.778 --> 36:46.226
We grow not only in crowd size but in maturity.

36:46.754 --> 36:57.707
And should we then need to take an eventual step to make more room for more people, we don't compromise maturity, we don't compromise doctrinal faithfulness, we don't compromise the mission that God has called us to be.

36:58.168 --> 37:05.336
Because we feel like we want to be a hub of gospel transformation in crazy California.

37:05.357 --> 37:07.219
We're right here in Fresno, California.

37:08.060 --> 37:16.530
There will be a place, and there are Lord willing many, but us on that list for sure that teach and train and equip.

37:16.674 --> 37:17.355
and disciple.

37:17.775 --> 37:24.563
So that, maybe by God's grace, when people in the Central Valley look around and go, I don't know what it is about those people, but they sure look like Christ.

37:25.324 --> 37:29.830
And they might have the audacity to call us Christians, Christ-like ones.

37:29.870 --> 37:30.751
Wouldn't that be beautiful?

37:31.512 --> 37:32.233
That's our intent.

37:32.253 --> 37:32.713
Let's pray.

37:33.354 --> 37:39.161
Father, thank you for the invitation that we have to teach and train and equip and disciple.

37:39.241 --> 37:40.463
Help us to be faithful to that.

37:41.204 --> 37:42.285
We can't do it without you.

37:42.986 --> 37:46.610
And so Lord, we want to be a place that's known

37:46.722 --> 37:58.416
Maybe years from now where people look back and say, well, that place was faithful to steward what you've entrusted to us and that we taught your word and we trained one another in maturity in Christ.

37:58.476 --> 38:00.819
And we equipped one another as to what the word says.

38:00.879 --> 38:04.183
And we made disciples because we were disciples.

38:04.964 --> 38:10.310
And so Lord, as we seek to deepen together, as we seek to focus on what's important, Lord, would you be with us?

38:10.430 --> 38:12.573
I pray and we'll thank you in Jesus name.

38:13.074 --> 38:13.394
Amen.

